task.summary: fixed issue #9 _ is not defined after multi-line command

added animated gif showing usage of n_
References: closes #11
got rid of anything grunt related; minor cosmetics
you can now enable FP mode via `$ n_ --fp`
implemented simple history persistence for the last session

persisting repl session history
For now the history is stored in a file named “.n_repl_history” in the user’s home directory. If some day in the future a sharable default emerges, this may be changed.
References:
https://github.com/tmpvar/repl.history/issues/6 closes #16
fix: using tar.gz package to “manually” unpack lodash@3 instead of npm-install-version
fix: using tar.gz package to “manually” unpack lodash@3 instead of npm-install-version - fixed test
fix: travis-ci was missing the postinstall step

fix: `$ n_3 --fp` now throws as FP-mode does not exist in lodash@3.10.1
References: closes #18

fix: all additional lodash versions are now stored in the folder extraneous
References: closes #19
